The paper deals with speaker verification, which is a subfield of speech processing and natural language processing. The use of Momentum Contrast (MoCo) for unsupervised representation learning and pretraining is a recent development in computer vision, but it has not been widely applied to speech processing. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves deep learning and representation learning, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
